If we assume that we know how to do the homework we are assigned, we should be able to complete it in a reasonable amount of time. But consider the schedules of many high school students: we often wake up early in the morning; some of us have long bus rides; and many of us have sports practices, jobs, or other extracurricular activities before or after school. We have to make time to eat dinner and complete our chores. Now add on three or more hours of homework a night and you have instant stress, not only for students but also for their families.

Parents

[/vc_column_text][distance type="2"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="2" animate="w-animate" blox_bgcolor="#f6f6f8"][vc_column width="2/3"][distance type="4"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" el_class="nopadd"]

Parents can play a vital role in helping teens succeed in school by being informed and lending a little support and guidance. Even though teens are seeking independence.

Everychild has the capacity to succeed in school and in life. Yet far too many children,especially those from poor and minority families, are placed at risk by school practices that are based on a sorting paradigm in which some students receive high-expectations instruction while the rest are relegatedto lower quality education and lower quality futures. The sorting perspective must bereplacedby a talent development model that asserts that all children are capable of succeeding ina rich and demanding curriculum with appropriate assistance and support.

[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="627" img_size="full" css_animation="appear"][distance][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" el_class="nopadd" css=".vc_custom_1467110808157{padding-top: 8px !important;}"]

Conceptualizing Parental Involvement

Therole of parents in managing childrens educational experiences at home and at school has long been considered critical for childrens success in school. However, it is only recently thatresearchers have begun systematic and extensive investigations of parental involvement beyond the early years of schooling. Recent research has investigated parents involvement in students education during the middle grades.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1467110059450{padding-left: 0px !important;}"][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1468235149153{padding-left: 0px !important;}" el_class="colorb"][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1468235156396{padding-top: 46px !important;padding-right: 33px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 40px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

Apply to Madison

[/vc_column_text][distance type="2"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="2" animate="w-animate" blox_bgcolor="#f6f6f8"][vc_column width="2/3" css=".vc_custom_1468738202791{padding-right: 0px !important;}"][distance type="4"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" el_class="nopadd"]

We consider academically motivated applicants. Admission is based on a combination of high school grades, rigor of courses taken, standardized test scores and a personal statement.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" el_class="nopadd"]

Completed applications are due January 15*, and families are notified of the admissions decision on March 10. Students whose applications are received after the deadline will be reviewed on a rolling basis as space allows.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" el_class="nopadd"]

To Madison, you are more than just a number. Youre more than an applicant reference number, more than a student number, and more than a high school average. Youre a scholar. You might be an athlete and you are definitely a leader in your school or community. Youre ready to change the world. At madison, were ready to help you do just that. If youve decided that madisonhigh school might just be for you, youre definitely in the right place.

[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1467543358259{padding-left: 0px !important;}"][vc_column_inner el_class="nopadleft" css=".vc_custom_1467543549179{padding-left: 0px !important;background-image: url(http://webnus.biz/themes/michigan/high-school/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/applay-01.jpg?id=854) !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;}"][distance type="5"][videoplay link="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jh5ZNwMIgjI?feature=oembed" size="32"][distance type="5"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][distance type="4"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1466331821326{padding-left: 0px !important;}" el_class="custom-btn-light"][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1468235614516{padding-left: 0px !important;}" el_class="colorb"][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1468235621956{padding-top: 46px !important;padding-right: 17px !important;padding-bottom: 60px !important;padding-left: 23px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

Get Ready

Apply for the 201617 school year

Check the required criteria & testing data Find the right enrollment option Review the tuition & financial information Attend one of the virtual open house

[/vc_column_text][button shape="rounded" btn_content="READ MORE" target="_blank" color="white" size="medium" border="true"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1468235641169{background-color: #323436 !important;}"][vc_column_inner el_class="custom-side-quote" css=".vc_custom_1468235799217{padding-top: 35px !important;padding-right: 7px !important;padding-bottom: 83px !important;padding-left: 14px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1466856097171{margin-bottom: 41px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}"]
The facilities and teachers are just great. Im so excited to use them all. Its like the dream school I ever wanted.
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1466856108824{padding-left: 21px !important;}"]

Daniel Smith Madison Student

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row animate="w-animate"][vc_column][distance type="5"][vc_column_text css_animation="appear" css=".vc_custom_1467544890819{margin-bottom: 35px !important;}"]

your application starts here: steps to apply

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1467544823245{margin-bottom: 26px !important;}"]

1. Choose Your Round:

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1467544881240{margin-bottom: 23px !important;}"]Which Round is Right for You?[/vc_column_text][ul type="circle"][li]The schools master schedule takes into consideration the time constraints of Round One applicants. The time constraints of Round Two applicants may not be considered in the final schedule, so it may be difficult for those applicants to attend certain courses.[/li][li]If you are seeking for financial aid, we strongly recommend applying in Round One. There will be limited financial aid available in Round Two[/li][li]Space in the school may be limited for Round Two applicants.[/li][/ul][distance type="2"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1467544931075{margin-bottom: 26px !important;}"]

2. Complete online application:

[/vc_column_text][ul type="circle"][li]When using the online application, you will be required to submit a 500 - 750 word personal statement describing why you want to attend the High School Program.[/li][li]Submit the application fee: A $50 non-refundable application fee, paid by credit card, is required at the time of submission of the online application form.[/li][/ul][distance type="2"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1467545111455{margin-bottom: 26px !important;}"]

3. Recommendations:

[/vc_column_text][ul type="circle"][li]Current English teacher.[/li][li]Current mathematics teacher.[/li][li]Special Interest or Personal Recommendation (optional).[/li][/ul][distance type="2"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1467545187819{margin-bottom: 26px !important;}"]

4. Check your Application Status:

[/vc_column_text][ul type="circle"][li] Keep an eye on your email. All communication from Madison will come through email.[/li][li]Watch your email for your Application Confirmation.
